item.description:
Timber makes it damn easy to use an image in a tag. Automatically, Timber will interpret images attached to a post&rsquo;s thumbnail field (&ldquo;Featured Image&rdquo; in the admin) and treat them as TimberImages. Then, in your Twig templates, you can access them via {{post.thumbnail}}. If you want to see what&rsquo;s inside the TimberImage object you can run a&hellip;
{{post.thumbnail|print_r}}  &hellip;inside one of your Twig templates.
Basic Image stuff Again, pretty damn easy:

You can set arbitrary locations for your twig files with&hellip;
&lt;?php /* functions.php */ Timber::$locations = '/Users/jared/Sandbox/templates';  Use the full file path to make sure Timber knows what you&rsquo;re trying to draw from. You can also send an array for multiple locations:
&lt;?php /* functions.php */ Timber::$locations = array(	'/Users/jared/Sandbox/templates', '~/Sites/timber-templates/', ABSPATH.'/wp-content/templates' );  You only need to do this once in your project (like in functions.php) then when you call from a PHP file (say single.
